news.title: UP-RERA informs allottees of five builders to file claims before IRP
news.para: UP-RERA has placed the pending complaints of the allottees as well as the proceedings of enforcement of its existing orders in ‘abeyance’.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani Group struggles to secure land to rehabilitate Dharavi residents
news.para: Only those who lived in Dharavi before the year 2000 will get free homes in the redevelopment and a lot of the land needed to rehabilitate people - at least 580 acres for now - will be to provide housing to the roughly 700,000 people considered ineligible.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders OSB Expressway Towers' builder to complete project in six months
news.para: The H-Rera met with homebuyers regarding the delayed OSB Expressway Towers project in Sector 109, Gurgaon, and issued a final warning. If the project isn't completed in six months, control may transfer to a buyers' association or involve a third-party builder. This action aims to protect buyers who've waited over seven years for their homes.

news.title: Builders in Uttar Pradesh who accepted rehabilitation deal but didn’t pay advance may lose land
news.para: Officials said Noida Authority was planning a three-pronged action – cancelling the lease deeds of defaulter projects, seizing land lying idle and taking over unsold inventory.

news.title: Delhi HC seeks status report on probe into Signature View Apartment lapses
news.para: The court asked the land-owning agency for an update after examining a letter sent to it by CBI in March last year, asking for certain details and a copy of a vigilance inquiry ordered by the lieutenant governor earlier.

news.title: NCDRC issues non-bailable warrant against Mantri Developers' founder
news.para: According to the order issued by the NCDRC on January 31, 2022, Mantri Estate Management Private Limited and others had collected Rs 7,12,86,650 from 302 flat owners.

news.title: FPCE writes to centre questioning MahaRERA move to set up forum to settle builder-buyer dispute
news.para: ​Forum for People's Collective Efforts' (FPCE) President Abhay Upadhyay has written a letter on August 19 to Union Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs Additional Secretary Satinder Pal Singh objecting to the conciliation forum constituted by MahaRERA and its "suspicious functioning".

news.title: Suraksha Group infuses Rs 250 crore in Jaypee Infratech
news.para: ​Around Rs 1,000 crore cash is lying in the balance sheet of the Jaypee Infratech Ltd, which the bankrupt company has accumulated from real estate business and toll income of Yamuna Expressway that connects Greater Noida and Agra.

news.title: PMAY built on mangrove zones in Navi Mumbai, environmentalists complain to PM
news.para: The PMAY projects, particularly in Mansarovar and Kharghar areas, have come up in proximity of mangroves, mudflats and inter-tidal wetlands, the complaint filed by NatConnect Foundation on PMO Public Grievance website states.

news.title: AIIB approves Rs 914 crore loan for Kochi metro phase II
news.para: The managing director of Kochi Metro Rail Limited (KMRL), Loknath Behera, said KMRL will sign a contract with the agency in Oct. As the funding procedures were delayed, the KMRL had started the initial works of the construction with funds sanctioned by the state govt in July first week.

news.title: Bombay HC contempt notice to Foremost Realtors for Rs 6 crore SRA rent paid claim
news.para: In June 2004, Dr Babasaheb Ambedkar Rahiwasi Seva Sangh SRA (proposed) and individual tenants entered into a redevelopment agreement with Satish Enterprises. The petition claimed that SRA permitted Foremost Realtors Pvt Ltd to replace it. In 2011, all their houses were demolished.

news.title: Gujarat government to regularise unauthorised constructions up to 4.5 FSI in rural areas
news.para: The Chief Minister has made a significant decision to make the IMPACT law more people-orientated in Gujarat, the CMO said.

news.title: Lucknow development body acquires more land for Edu City
news.para: The committee formed by LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar started the process of signing agreements with farmers in the Pyarepur village on a consensual basis 15 days ago.

news.title: Properties in Pune availing tax rebates for rainwater harvesting up ten times in decade
news.para: According to civic data, only 306 properties availed tax benefits (just for rainwater harvesting) in 2012-2013. The number rose to 3,716 in 2022-2023.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to offer leasehold properties in sector 39
news.para: The administration, which was in final stages of auctioning the shop-cum-office (SCO) sites in the new market on a freehold basis, is now reworking the plan, bringing it in lines with the MHA directions.

news.title: Draft notification on eco-sensitive zones open to feedback: Goa CM
news.para: “Forty days are left to submit objections and suggestions to the environment ministry,” chief minister Pramod Sawant said on Friday. He said that once again he will write to Union govt to notify only 63 villages as ESAs.

news.title: Group of ministers in favour of bare minimum GST on housing: Goa CM
news.para: This was one of the issues chiefly discussed in the (GoMs) meeting on Thursday, Sawant said. GoMs, Sawant said, also laid the thrust on the need to boost the real estate sector under GST.

news.title: Gurugram: Two illegal buildings razed, 14 plots sealed in Saraswati Kunj
news.para: The operation was part of an ongoing effort by GMDA and Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) to curb unauthorised construction and illegal commercial activities in the area

news.title: BlackRock leases 42,700 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: The financial institution’s India arm Blackrock Services India will be paying rental of Rs 325 per sq ft a month in the first year of the lease. The agreement includes a clause to escalate rentals by 5% in April 2025, by 10% a year after that and 5% each in 2027 and 2028.

news.title: Suraksha Group awards tenders for 41 towers of Jaypee Infratech projects
news.para: For the remaining 56 towers, Suraksha is expected to finalise contractors by Sept. This comes as a major relief to over 10,000 homebuyers who are waiting over a decade for their homes in various JIL projects.
